living-concrete.pattern:
Each scene in a blueprint:

```
SCENE: {title}
MODE: {P|A|C|E|R}
PURPOSE: {what reader gains}
CONTENT: {key points, 2-4 bullets}
DEPENDS: {prior scenes required}
TRANSITIONS: {from previous mode, to next mode}
```

Keep scenes atomic -- one cognitive mode per scene. Mixed-mode scenes
produce confused processing. If a section needs both concept and evidence,
split into two scenes.
